Sentece: In the single dose studies, mean values of elimination rate constant (0.0155h) and clearance (1.85L/h) for untreated subjects were different from those for the pretreated subjects (0.0375h and 5.10L/h), while the apparent volumes of distribution did not differ significantly between the two groups (120.3L vs 140.8L).
